consent: Thank you for taking the time to participate in our study. This study will examine your perceptions on chemical reactivity, and should take around 15 minutes to complete. Your participation is entirely voluntary, and no compensation, monetary or otherwise, will be given. Please note that you can choose to withdraw your participation at any time for any reason. You will not be asked to submit any identifying information, nor will any information of that sort be recorded (name, location, IP address, etc.), and the publication of study results will be anonymous.
before_start:
We would recommend maximizing your browser window and if possible avoid distractions for the duration of the session


Read each statement below and check the boxes, if applicable:
acad_years: How many years did you study in academia? (incl. all academic degrees and certificates)
degree: What is your highest academic degree/title?
indus_exp: Do you have any experience in the Chemical industry? (i.e., outside of academia)
indus_exp_years:
How many years did you work in the industry?

(If your answer can only be given as months, please select "1")
status: Currently, what is your position at your place of employment? (e.g., lecturer, PI, researcher, etc.)
institu: In what kind of institution do you work? (University, College, Chemical industry, start-up, etc.)
org_chem: In the past three months, how many papers did you read concerning organic chemistry?
org-react: In the past three months, how many papers did you read concerning organocatalytic reactions?
org_chem_proj: In the past three months, have you been involved in a project concerning organic chemistry? (involved = guiding, counseling or writing)
org_react_proj: In the past three months, have you been involved in a project concerning organocatalytic reactions? (involved = guiding, counseling or writing)
ideas: Finally, please share any thoughts or ideas that came to you regarding the study during your participation, or that you think may be important to the research team.
